    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An an early, widely used 3-D printing technology. It is a process that builds 3-D objects by converting liquid materials into solid parts by curing them using a light source, which causes chains of molecules to link, forming polymers. The process is used for creating models, prototypes, patterns, and production parts. A typical method uses a UV laser to create cross-sections of the object within a vat of liquid photopolymer. The process was first developed in 1986. The process is valued to create accurate parts with repeatable dimensions; applications include engineering assemblies, jewelry casting, and dental repairs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047273/Penn State Learning Center (2005)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047274/Milwaukee School of Engineering [online] (2005)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proceso de prototipo rápido que construye objetos tridimensionales usando un laser UV para crear las partes representativas del objeto. Los polímeros solidifican cuando están expuestos a la luz UV. El proceso fue desarrollado en 1986, y las piezas creadas por este proceso son generalmente frágiles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In 1986 ontwikkeld rapid prototyping-proces waarbij driedimensionale objecten worden geconstrueerd door middel van een UV-laser die dwarsdoorsneden van het object binnen een vat met vloeibare fotopolymeren opbouwt. Bij blootstelling aan UV-licht harden de polymeren uit. De met dit procedé vervaardigde delen zijn doorgaans nogal kwetsbaar.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>為快速成型技術的製作過程，從大量的感光性樹脂之中，使用紫外線雷射製作出物件的橫斷面，以建構出3D立體物件。此樹脂聚合物暴露於紫外線下時即可固化。此種製作過程發展於西元1986年間，且一般而言，以此項過程製造出的組件質地相當脆弱。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
